cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "jlenskit: a reproducible toolkit for the Jacobian lens (J-lens)"
message: "If you use this software, please cite both the software and the paper it implements."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Sam
    family-names: Chen
repository-code: "https://github.com/SamC1249/j-lens"
url: "https://github.com/SamC1249/j-lens"
abstract: >-
  jlenskit is a modular, reproducible toolkit for fitting and applying the
  Jacobian lens (J-lens) to open-weights decoder language models. It estimates
  the corpus-averaged input->output Jacobian per layer, decodes hidden states
  into vocabulary space through the model's own final norm and unembedding, and
  ships structured outputs, an offline HTML viewer, and provenance manifests.
keywords:
  - interpretability
  - mechanistic-interpretability
  - jacobian-lens
  - transformers
  - large-language-models
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
references:
  - type: article
    title: "Verbalizable Representations Form a Global Workspace in Language Models"
    authors:
      - name: "Anthropic"
    year: 2026
    url: "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/workspace/index.html"
    notes: "The paper that introduces the Jacobian lens; jlenskit is an independent implementation."
